Now te St Michael’s church the mourners bear
Her dust ; a train of Poor would see the end
Of one who blest them with an angel’s care ;

Weeping, they watch the funeral of their friend,
Old men and little children gathered there.

In speechless sorrow o’er her tomb we bend ;
Farewell, farewell, till all the years are run;
Farewell, farewell, till our own course is done.

